  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: SixthDayConvo01
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: SixthDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: There you are! Right on schedule. Contractually enforced punctuality--
      my favorite kind!
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Day six! It all feels routine by now, yes? You know, some contract workers
      only work five days-- well, five nights. Not you, though.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Anyway, your work has been meeting my expectations so far, so good job!
      Although that\u2019s not saying much, because my expectations for you are quite
      low."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: But, just keep doing your best work, and you could have a longer future
      here than I thought. Longer than most of our guests, anyway.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Tonight, I need you to pull in <b>[$quota]</b>. The gift shop\u2019s been
      seeing more... discerning customers lately, so don\u2019t just grab anything.
      Quality over quantity-- though both are preferred."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "You have many tools at your disposal now, but I\u2019m sure you\u2019re
      just <i>itching</i> for a new tool, yes? Well, itch no longer."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "This one\u2019s great for extracting the more... sought-after bits. The
      kind customers whisper about. Here, take it-- it\u2019s a <b>scooper</b>. Like
      an ice-cream scooper, but for scooping <b>eyeballs</b> instead of ice-cream."
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
